  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>lowdisc_cget</refname>
    <refpurpose>  Returns the value associated with the given key for the given Random Number object.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>value = lowdisc_cget(this,key)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>this</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>The current Random Number object.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>key</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>
            The name of the option to get.
            All options which can be set with lowdisc_configure
            can be get with lowdisc_cget.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>value</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>The value associated with the key.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This command allows to get the current state of the Random Number object, which has be configure with the lowdisc_configure command.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <para>
      In the following script, one declares a new Random Number object.
      This object is associated with the Park and Miller generator.
    </para>
    <programlisting role="example">
      rng = lowdisc_new();
      rng = lowdisc_configure(rng,"-method","parkmiller");
      method = lowdisc_cget(rng,"-method");
    </programlisting>
  </refsection>
